-- Manchester United Ties Aston Villa 2-2 to Stay Unbeaten in Premier League
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2010-11-13T14:50:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-13/manchester-united-ties-aston-villa-2-2-to-stay-unbeaten-in-premier-league.html
Manchester United rallied to tie
Aston Villa 2-2 and remain undefeated in English soccer’s
Premier League.  Federico Macheda and Nemanja Vidic scored in the final nine
minutes for United at Villa Park in Birmingham. The Red Devils,
who’ve won six and drawn seven this season, are second in the
standings, three points behind Chelsea.  Ashley Young and Marc Albrighton scored for Villa, which
moves up to sixth place.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  